<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1058,1217,1407]" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" box="[458,545,1218,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pyticara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="974" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,545,1218,1239]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">Pyticara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
SPINOLA was revised in 2015 (
<bibRefCitation author="OPITZ W" box="[862,996,1217,1239]" pageId="15" pageNumber="974" pagination="711 - 730" refId="ref53607" refString="OPITZ W. (2015 a): Classification, natural history, and evolution of the Enopliinae GISTEL (Coleoptera: Cleridae). Part IV. The New World genus Pyticara SPINOLA. - Linzer biologische Beitrage 47 (1): 711 - 730." type="journal article" year="2015">OPITZ 2015a</bibRefCitation>
). This work included a key to species. 
<taxonomicName box="[480,692,1245,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pyticara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="974" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontegalba">
<emphasis box="[480,692,1245,1267]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">Pyticara frontegalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens key out to 
<emphasis box="[922,1058,1245,1267]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">P. championi</emphasis>
GORHAM from which 
<taxonomicName box="[386,536,1273,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pyticara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="974" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontegalba">
<emphasis box="[386,536,1273,1295]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">P. frontegalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens differ by showing a longer combined length of the funicular antennomeres. In 
<taxonomicName box="[576,725,1301,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pyticara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="974" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontegalba">
<emphasis box="[576,725,1301,1323]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">P. frontegalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens the combined length of the funicular antennomeres are longer that 1/2 of the length of the basal capitular antennomeres. In 
<emphasis box="[351,496,1357,1379]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">P. championi</emphasis>
specimens, the combined length of the funicular antennomeres are shorter than 1/2 the length of the basal antennomere of the capitulum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1059,1421,1583]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1059,210,316]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="975" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 13.0 mm; width 6.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[962,1052,1421,1443]" captionStart="Figs 282-285" captionStartId="98.[151,191,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[153,1059,199,1489]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[153,1059,199,1491]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="Figs 282-285: Habitus; (282) Parapelonides naranjo; (283) Pyticara frontegalba; (284) Amboakis bermejo; (285) A. collucoatis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746802/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">Fig. 283</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium and prothorax yellow; antenna black; pterothorax brown; elytra bicolorous, anterior 1/4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[390,403,1473,1487]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">th</superScript>
yellow, posterior 3/4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[621,634,1473,1487]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">th</superScript>
black; prothoracic and mesothoracic legs bicolorous, femora yellow, tibiae and tarsi brown, metathoracic legs brown; abdomen black. Head: Eyes small, coarsely facetted, eye much narrower than frons (EW/FW 52/70); funicular antennomeres (
<figureCitation box="[486,561,1561,1583]" captionStart="Figs 28-42" captionStartId="71.[151,191,1299,1321]" captionTargetBox="[152,1047,199,1264]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[152,1059,199,1284]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="Figs 28-42: Antennae; (28) Neorthopleura thomasi, male; (29) N. thomasi, female; (30) N. subfasciata, male; (31) Artoadenus atrafinus; (32) Neorthopleura subfasciata, female; (33) Akonesis atraordinis; (34) Pelonium erudiatum; (35) Neorthopleura cuspidis, female; (36) Agnatis curvabilis; (37) Ichnea paraguayensis; (38) Neorthopleura quintana, male; (39) Pyticara frontegalba; (40) Platynoptera potaro; (41) Neorthopleura cuspidis, male; (42) Nanoclerus fuscus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746748/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="974">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) transverse, very setose; capitular antennomeres 9 and 10 long rectangulate, antennomere 11 very oblong ovate. Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 179-193" captionStartId="81.[151,191,1359,1381]" captionTargetBox="[167,1032,201,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@81.[152,1058,201,1346]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="Figs 179-193: Pronota; 179) Phonius versus; (180) Perilypus arsus; (181) A. nodus; (182) Pyticara frontegalba; (183) Pelonium implacide; (184) Neorthoplera quintana; (185) Perilypus virgulatus; (186) P. alpinus; (187) Amboakis expandosa; (188) Ampleris jatai; (189) Megaphloeus jasuni; (190) Amboakis bermejo (191) Madoniella delta; (192) Megaphloeus imparilus; (193) Pyticeroides brevitubulus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746768/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Fig. 182</figureCitation>
) transverse; pronotal tubercles absent (PW/PL 210/180), disc finely punctate; elytral disc without asetiferous punctures, elytra notably flared in posterior 1/2 (EL/EW 700/200). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse/scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[846,934,294,316]" captionStart="Figs 213-218" captionStartId="85.[151,191,1262,1284]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="Figs 213-218: Aedeagi; (213) Perilypus virgulatus; (214) Agnatis curvabilis; (215) A. vaurieae; (216) Parapelonides naranjo; (217) Pyticara frontegalba; (218) Amboakis bermejo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746776/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Fig. 217</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1058,330,380]" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">
Variation: Length 13.0- 
<quantity box="[394,488,330,352]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="16" pageNumber="975" unit="mm" value="16.5">16.5 mm</quantity>
; width 3.5-7.0 mm. The extent of the yellow region on the elytral base varies.
</paragraph>
