<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1058,466,544]" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[542,660,466,487]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">frontegalba</emphasis>
, is a Latin compound name that stems from 
<emphasis box="[212,278,494,515]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">frontis</emphasis>
(= forepart) and 
<emphasis box="[474,542,494,515]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">galbus</emphasis>
(= yellow); with regard to yellow color of the anterior dorsal 1/2 of this beetle.
</paragraph>
